HEADWORD: Glimmering
<hw>Glim"mer*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Faint, unsteady
light; a glimmer.</def> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A faint view or idea; a glimpse; an
inkling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>glimmery</ent>⟦br⟧
